# Action Items for Technical Writing Co-op Launch

---

## 1. Finalize Business Plan  
- **Action:** Review and complete each section of the business plan outline  
- **Owner:** All founding members  
- **Due Date:** July 10, 2025  
- **Notes:** Assign leads for each section; schedule review meeting

---

## 2. Register Co-op Entity  
- **Action:** Research and file legal paperwork for co-op registration  
- **Owner:** Legal/Administrative Lead  
- **Due Date:** July 20, 2025  
- **Notes:** Consult local co-op development center for guidance

---

## 3. Draft Bylaws and Member Agreements  
- **Action:** Create initial drafts for bylaws and agreements  
- **Owner:** Governance Committee  
- **Due Date:** July 25, 2025  
- **Notes:** Circulate drafts for member feedback

---

## 4. Develop Compensation & Profit-Sharing Model  
- **Action:** Design transparent pay and profit-sharing structure  
- **Owner:** Finance/HR Team  
- **Due Date:** July 30, 2025  
- **Notes:** Consider experience, education, and contribution

---

## 5. Build Website and Portfolio  
- **Action:** Set up website, showcase member bios and sample work  
- **Owner:** Marketing Team  
- **Due Date:** August 5, 2025  
- **Notes:** Use open-source tools; highlight co-op values

---

## 6. Outreach & Member Recruitment  
- **Action:** Launch outreach campaign to attract new members  
- **Owner:** Outreach Lead  
- **Due Date:** August 10, 2025  
- **Notes:** Target professional networks, universities, and online communities

---

## 7. Secure Initial Clients  
- **Action:** Identify and approach potential clients  
- **Owner:** Sales/Client Relations Team  
- **Due Date:** August 20, 2025  
- **Notes:** Prepare pitch materials and service packages

---

## 8. Set Up Collaboration Tools  
- **Action:** Choose and configure project management and communication platforms  
- **Owner:** Operations Lead  
- **Due Date:** August 1, 2025  
- **Notes:** Prioritize open-source and privacy-respecting tools

---

## 9. Schedule First General Meeting  
- **Action:** Organize inaugural member meeting to ratify bylaws and elect roles  
- **Owner:** All founding members  
- **Due Date:** August 15, 2025  
- **Notes:** Prepare agenda and voting procedures

---

## 10. Establish Financial Accounts  
- **Action:** Open co-op bank account and set up bookkeeping  
- **Owner:** Finance Lead  
- **Due Date:** August 5, 2025  
- **Notes:** Research co-op-friendly banks and accounting software

---

## 11. Develop Marketing Materials  
- **Action:** Create brochures, slide decks, and social media profiles  
- **Owner:** Marketing Team  
- **Due Date:** August 10, 2025  
- **Notes:** Emphasize collective expertise and co-op values

---

## 12. Plan Ongoing Training & Peer Support  
- **Action:** Design mentorship and professional development programs  
- **Owner:** HR/Training Lead  
- **Due Date:** August 25, 2025  
- **Notes:** Schedule regular workshops and peer review sessions

---

**Tips:**  
- Review and update action items weekly.  
- Assign clear owners and track progress.  
- Foster open communication and collective problem-solving.